CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 18, 1961, pg. 26 reads: "Emphasis On Voter Registrations - The Pittsburgh Civic League urges all non-registered citizens to register immediately. The last day to register is March 27.  Further, those persons, who have changed their addresses, should notify the Registration Commission of this change at once.  Many thousands of potential voters in city are not registered to vote.  Voting is an important civic duty, for which people have given their lives.  The  offers its help to those persons who need assistance.  The league's registration committee is composed of the following members: Third Ward, James McCoy; Fifth Ward, John Grice; 13th Ward, Donald Clayton; 15th Ward, James Ward; 18th Ward, Orlando Sells, Douglas King is chairman of the Pittsburgh Civic League.  Members shown in above picture, are, left to right, standing: Orlando Sells, James Moss, Jesse DelGre, Linwood Brosier.  Seated: Mary Gloster, John Grice, Christine Cawthon. - Harris photo.'
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Pittsburgh Civic League registration committee, from left, seated: Mary Gloster, John Grice, and Christine Cawthon; standing: Orlando Sells, James Moss, Jesse DelGre, and Linwood Brosier, posed in interior with light colored curtain room divider on right
